#############################################################################
#  WARNING							 	    #
#									    #
#  Configure freedwall.conf before doing "make install"			    #
#									    #
#############################################################################

REQUISITI:
Following options must be enabled in the kernel:

[kernel 2.4]
NETWORKING OPTIONS ->
	IP: NETFILTER CONFIGURATION ->
		[*] Connection tracking
		[*] IP tables support
		[*] limit match support
		[*] stealth match support (solo con grsecurity)
		[*] Connection state match support
		[*] Unclean match support
		[*] Packet filtering
		[*] REJECT tartget support
		[*] LOG target support

[kernel 2.6]
DEVICE DRIVERS ->
	NETWORKING SUPPORT ->
		NETWORKING OPTIONS ->
			NETWORK PACKET FILTERING ->
				IP:NETFILTER CONFIGURATION
					[*] Connection tracking
					[*] IP tables support
					[*] limit match support
					[*] stealth match support (solo grsec)
					[*] Connection state match support
					[*] Packet filtering
					[*] REJECT tartget support
					[*] LOG target support



INSTALL:
- edit freedwall.conf
- type "make install" and press return

USAGE:
- to load firewall: "/etc/init.d/freedwall start"
- to stop firewall: "/etc/init.d/freedwall stop"
- to reload firewall: "/etc/init.d/freedwall reload"


That's all folks.


